Comment:
Hi everyone!

I feel honoured!  A Master who I had never played or before with a rating of 2345, sent me a challenge!  Despite the fact that I had all the extra games I accepted the challenge with some gusto.  Maybe, after being Freddied quite often you could say that I was a glutton for punishment though!  He gave me the Lopez, I was considering playing the Open Lopez but after the debacle with Dave I really wanted to redeem myself somehow.  The first 7 moves follow Autopilot Part 1, but on the 7th move I played the Main Line d6.  I still stuck to that bally DB like the proverbial limpet though!
8. c3 - I decided to pick up the action here.  This move is played to allow an escape square for his lsb should I decide to play Na5 and not wish to allow it to be exchanged on b3.

26. ...... f5 - suddenly I feel cold and the air becomes putrid and there is a dark, dark shadow over me.  It is also right over Henry and is threatening to descend on h7.  What is this?  Well, you readers have guessed it by now - it is the chessic Grim Reaper - Old Matey!
27. Qf4 - nasty, nasty.

28. Re7 - here I resign the game on the grounds of ruinous loss of material.  I am already a pawn down and the pawn on g2 must now drop and I have a terrible feeling that Old Matey cannot be too far away (although Jeff did not announce it).  So I waved the white flag.  Another disappointing show from The Beginner with the Class A Rating.
